h the reasons for this association are not clear."],"variants":[{"name":"Cecelia","meanings":["From the Latin name <i>Caecilia</i>, feminine form of <i>Caecilius</i> (  see  Cecil  ). This was a good deal more common than the masculine form, largely due to the fame of the 2nd- or 3rd-century virgin martyr whose name is still mentioned daily in the Roman Catholic Canon of the Mass. She is regarded as the patron saint of music and has inspired works such as  Purcell's  ‘Ode on St Cecilia's Day’, although the reasons for this association are not clear."]}]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Cecilia of Bar-sur-Seine was born in 1083, in France. She married Ralph de Langetot in 1108, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 3 daughters. She died about 1160, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 78."},"et":{"1083–about 1160":"1083–umbes 1160","1080–1126":"1080–1126","1108–Female":"1108–Surnud","1112–1185":"1112–1185","1114–Female":"1114–Surnud","1116–Male":"1116–Surnud","1118–Male":"1118–Surnud","1083–1160":"1083–1160","1080":"1080","about 1160":"umbes 1160","1185":"1185","1083":"1083","1160":"1160","1118":"1118","1116":"1116","30 July 1126":"30. juuli 1126","1126":"1126","1114":"1114","about 1108":"umbes 1108","1112":"1112","1108":"1108","Calvados, Basse-Normandie, France":"Calvados, Basse-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","France":"Prantsusmaa","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Compton Gifford, Devonshire, England":"Compton Gifford, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1083–about 1160":"1083–noin 1160","1080–1126":"1080–1126","1108–Female":"1108–Kuollut","1112–1185":"1112–1185","1114–Female":"1114–Kuollut","1116–Male":"1116–Kuol